data.enText: connected with the culture of a particular society or group, its customs, beliefs, etc.

data.chText: 这两种社群之间的文化差异
data.enText: cultural differences between the two communities

data.chText: 与艺术、文学、音乐等有关的
data.enText: connected with art, literature, music, etc.

data.chText: 管弦乐队对这座城市的文化生活而言非常重要。
data.enText: The orchestra is very important for the cultural life of the city.

word_means: 与艺术、文学、音乐等有关的

means: 与艺术、文学、音乐等有关的

tr: denoting or deriving from or distinctive of the ways of living built up by a group of people
example: influenced by ethnic and cultural ties"- J.F.Kenned

tr: relating to the raising of plants or animals
of or relating to the shared knowledge and values of a society
of or relating to the arts and manners that a group favors
example: a person of broad cultural interests

value.def: Cultural means relating to a particular society and its ideas, customs, and art.

example.ex: ...a deep sense of personal honor which was part of his cultural heritage.
example.tran: 他所继承的文化传统中强烈的个人荣誉感

example.ex: ...the Rajiv Gandhi Foundation which promotes cultural and educational exchanges between Britain and India.
example.tran: 促进英国和印度两国文化和教育交流的拉吉夫·甘地基金会

example.ex: ...an informed guide to culturally and historically significant sites...
example.tran: 详细介绍著名文化和历史景点的指南

example.ex: Culturally, they have much in common with their neighbours just across the border.
example.tran: 在文化上，他们与边境那边相邻而居的人们有许多共同点。

value.def: Cultural means involving or concerning the arts.

example.ex: ...the sponsorship of sports and cultural events by tobacco companies.
example.tran: 烟草公司对体育赛事和文化活动的赞助

example.ex: ...one of our better-governed, culturally active regional centres—Manchester or Birmingham, say.
example.tran: 我们管理更出色、艺术活动较活跃的区域性中心之一——比如说曼彻斯特或伯明翰

trans: (尤指对于不同态度和价值观的)文化意识
